  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "PAN Card: I lost my Aadhaar card. How can I get a second copy?",
  "response": "If you have lost your Aadhaar card, you can easily obtain a duplicate copy by following these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the UIDAI Website**: Go to the official website of the Unique Identification Authority of India (UIDAI) at [uidai.gov.in](https://uidai.gov.in).\n\n2. **Download Aadhaar from UIDAI Portal**: \n   - On the homepage, look for the option labeled **\"Download Aadhaar\"**.\n   - You will be asked to enter your **Aadhaar number or Enrollment ID**. If you don\u2019t have your Aadhaar number, you can use your **registered mobile number** to receive an OTP (One Time Password).\n\n3. **Authentication**: \n   - Enter the OTP sent to your registered mobile number for authentication.\n   - Once authenticated, you can download a digital version of your Aadhaar card, which is considered valid.\n\n4. **Aadhaar Reprint**: \n   - If you need a physical copy, you can choose to have your Aadhaar reprinted.\n   - On the UIDAI website, look for the **\"Order Aadhaar Reprint\"** option. You will need to pay a nominal fee for the reprint.\n   - Provide your Aadhaar number, enter the OTP sent to your registered mobile number, and make the payment.\n\n5. **Check Aadhaar Status**: After ordering a reprint, you can track the status of your Aadhaar reprint on the UIDAI website.\n\n6. **Download Using the mAadhaar App**: Alternatively, you can also use the mAadhaar mobile app to download your Aadhaar card. Just install the app, complete the on-screen instructions, and follow the process to retrieve your Aadhaar.\n\nMake sure that your mobile number is registered with your Aadhaar, as OTP verification is a crucial step in this process. If your mobile number is not linked or you do not have access to it, you will need to visit an Aadhaar Enrolment Centre for assistance.",
